.TH "WEBGL_lose_context.restoreContext" "JS" "July 7, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WEBGL_lose_context.restoreContext \- WEBGL_lose_context:
restoreContext() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]WEBGL_lose_context.restoreContext()\f[R] method is part of the
WebGL API and allows you to simulate restoring the context of a
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext\f[R] object.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
restoreContext()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
Browsers may not report WebGL errors by default.
WebGL\[cq]s error reporting works by calling \f[CR]getError()\f[R] and
checking for errors.
The following exceptions may be thrown:
.TP
\f[B]INVALID_OPERATION\f[R]
Thrown if the context was not lost.
.SH EXAMPLES
With this method, you can simulate the \f[CR]webglcontextrestored\f[R]
event:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] gl = canvas.getContext(\[dq]webgl\[dq]);

canvas.addEventListener(
  \[dq]webglcontextrestored\[dq],
  (e) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    console.log(e);
  },
  \f[B]false\f[R],
);

gl.getExtension(\[dq]WEBGL_lose_context\[dq]).restoreContext();
.EE
